==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spagyrist
<hw>Spag"y*rist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>spagiriste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A chemist, esp. one
devoted to alchemistic pursuits.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of a sect which arose in the days of alchemy,
who sought to discover remedies for disease by chemical means. The
spagyrists historically preceded the iatrochemists.</def> <rj><au>Encyc.
Brit.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

